      "note_no": "19",
      "note": "In the generally-accepted reading, this phrase is spelled li-mustaqarrin laha, which may be rendered as above or, more conventionally, as \"to its point of rest\", i.e., the time (or point) of the daily sunset (Razi). However, 'Abd Allah ibn Mas'ud is reliably reported to have read these words as la mustaqarra laha (Zamakhshari), which gives us the meaning of \"it runs [on its course] without having any rest\", i.e., unceasingly."
